      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "MARY ANNE ROSE (8) headed north off a win from wider on this row at Penrith then performed strongly in a higher-graded race at this circuit and distance last time out, working for a 1.2m second. Draws for a trail and the sprint lane is in play. Big chance. EUREKA JO (7) placed here two back then led and boxed on when beaten 4.3m last week. That was her first time out of the top-three in five attempts at this distance. Draws wide but looks close to a win. QUEEN LILIBET (2) had a tough draw last week but is much better served this time having won from this barrier two back at this circuit and distance. CANADIAN LASS NZ (3) draws much better than last start and recorded close seconds in the previous two outings at this circuit and distance, one from this barrier.",
